added.title: The Scoop
added.description: The Titans find it odd when Starfire becomes friends with an ice cream scoop.

added.title: Chicken in the Cradle
added.description: Beast Boy neglects his responsibilities, leaving the other Titans to raise his baby chick.

added.title: Kabooms Part 1
added.description: The Titans are excited to see the movie version of their favorite show "Babies vs Dogs".

added.title: Kabooms Part 2
added.description: Inspired by the "Babies vs Dogs" movie, the Titans decide to make a big Hollywood film of their own.

added.title: Tower Renovation
added.description: Following the destruction of their Tower by Slade, the Titans go house hunting.

added.title: My Name Is Jose
added.description: The Titans have Raven give them new super powers but have a hard time adjusting.

added.title: The Power of Shrimps
added.description: Aqualad uses shrimps and prime rib to win back Raven.

added.title: Monster Squad!
added.description: The Titans want to be the scariest trick-or-treaters in town, so Raven casts a spell to turn them into real monsters.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: Quantum Fun
added.description: Robin takes the other Titans on a trip through the dizzying world of quantum physics.

added.title: BBRBDAY
added.description: When he isn't invited to Beast Boy's birthday party, Robin throws his own party, with special guest Bob Uecker.

added.title: Slapping Butts and Celebrating for No Reason
added.description: When the Big Game is threatened the Titans must infiltrate the football stadium and stop the attack.

added.title: Nostalgia Is Not a Substitute for an Actual Story
added.description: The Titans time travel back to the 1980s to determine whether or not it was the best decade ever.

added.title: Business Ethics Wink Wink
added.description: Starfire dreams of becoming a successful business alien princess and joins a cookie-selling organization to learn the proper skills.

added.title: Genie President
added.description: Robin hatches a plan to get rich off pennies, but Starfire believes they are magical.

added.title: The Rival
added.description: The Wattersons look back on Anais' first days in the Watterson house. Gumball and Darwin quickly find themselves up an opponent who is able to outsmart them at every turn.

added.title: The Lady
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin track a women emerging from their home, they discover her to be a member of a gang of wise-cracking elderly friends. However, as they get closer and closer to her life, they realize they may know her already.

added.title: The Sucker
added.description: Gumball spends the day with Bomb Kid, who has decided Gumball is the perfect target for him and his friends to play pranks on. However he soon learns that Gumball is so gullible that pranks bounce off him.

added.title: The Vegging
added.description: Gumball and Darwin want to have a lazy day on the sofa, and have come up with various tricks to stop themselves having to move. Gradually more and more people arrive, seemingly to get them to move, until finally they realize that if they have to move, they'll do it in the laziest way possible.

added.title: The One
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are joking around, but when Tobias joins in and makes fun of Gumball, he's incredibly offended. They explain to Tobias that to make those jokes he'd need to be higher on Gumball's friend list. They think that's the end of it, but Tobias is after that number one spot.

added.title: The Father
added.description: When Frankie attends a party at The Watterson's he realizes it's a holiday Granny Jojo made up to celebrate the day he left. Richard is feeling sad about the years he lost with Frankie so the kids try anything to cheer him up.

added.title: The Cringe
added.description: When the uncomfortableness between them reaches new levels, Gumball and Hot Dog Guy decide they have to confront their ongoing awkwardness by making things as awkward as possible.

added.title: The Cage
added.description: When Mr. Corneille shows up to work with a mysterious bruise, Gumball and Darwin discover that he's teacher by day and a cage fighter by night, or was until he vowed never to fight again. However, when the school is being closed for a lack of finances the boys have to try and convince him to come out retirement for one last fight.

added.title: The Faith
added.description: Everything in Elmore is suddenly just various shades of grey, and things all over town are going wrong. Gumball and Darwin follow the mayhem and learn that one person was holding the whole town together: Alan. They have to restore his faith in the world to bring color back to Elmore.

added.title: The Candidate
added.description: When their parents all go to a charity gala at the school, the kids are locked in a classroom with a VHS tape. However, when the room starts to heat up, they need a leader to get them out of the situation and have to choose between Anais, a qualified but unpopular candidate or Gumball, a charismatic candidate with absolutely no plans.

added.title: The Anybody
added.description: Gumball wants Clayton to sit his detention for him, so he convinces him it's way more exciting to be take the shapes of other people.  However, Clayton begins imitating people all over town and causing mayhem. Gumball and Darwin have to convince him that the most exciting person to be is himself.

added.title: The Pact
added.description: Gumball finds Penny's laugh annoying, but can't think of a way to tell her without offending her. When he discovers that Principal Brown has the same problem with Miss Simian's morning breath, they decide to swap problems to save themselves from getting dumped.

added.title: The Neighbor
added.description: When their neighbor tries to bring over a package for them, Gumball and Darwin realize they have never learned his name, and it's way too late to ask. They try everything to figure out what it is, but when they do they find out there are bigger secrets to learn about their neighbor than just his name...

added.title: The Shippening
added.description: When people that barely know each other start falling in love, Gumball thinks he knows who's behind it. He rushes to Sarah's house and finds her writing in a magic notebook that turns everything in it into reality. When everything in Elmore gets crazier and crazier there's only one thing for it: they have to write their way out.

added.title: The Brain
added.description: Anais has been facepalming every time her family does something stupid, which has led to a serious medical condition. In fact, if she facepalms just one more time she could do her brain irreparable damage, so the Wattersons have to get through the week without doing anything idiotic.

added.title: The Ground Is Lava!
added.description: When an intense game of "The Ground is Lava" breaks out, Craig must carefully traverse the Creek to save his sister.

added.title: Council of the Creek: Operation Hive-Mind
added.description: Hive Mind - When bees take over the Trading Tree, Craig must assemble the Council of the Creek to avert disaster.

added.title: The Bike Thief
added.description: Craig investigates the theft of the 10 Speed's bikes in hopes of finding the culprit!

added.title: Craig of the Beach
added.description: Craig gets to hit the beach with his friends and family, but starts to get worried his Dad is more fun than him.

added.title: Plush Kingdom
added.description: Craig, Kelsey, JP and Jessica discover a group of plushie obsessed kids, deep within the creek.

added.title: The Ice Pop Trio
added.description: Craig sets out in search of Ice Pops on a hot day with the help of an unlikely duo.

added.title: Pencil Break Mania
added.description: When Pencil Break Mania hits the Creek, JP finds himself as an unlikely champion and is forced to defend his title against the very best!

added.title: The Last Game of Summer
added.description: It's the last day of summer, and the last chance for Craig to uncover an ancient treasure beneath the Creek.

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: Afterschool Snackdown
added.description: Craig enters a food competition in the Creek but worries he may be out of his league.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: Craig finds himself being chased by a monster in the Creek that's straight out of the movies!

added.title: King of Camping
added.description: The Williams Family goes camping and Craig helps his dad prove he's the King of Camping.

added.title: The Rise and Fall of the Green Poncho
added.description: Craig tries to warn his friends about the Other Side of the Creek with a tale from the Creek's defender - the Green Poncho.

added.title: I Don't Need a Hat
added.description: Craig decides to ditch his hat on a chilly day and it becomes a battle for body heat.

added.title: Alternate Creekiverse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP imagine a disturbing alternate reality where they never became friends!

added.title: Big Trouble Little Babies
added.description: When they realize they're too small for the rides at an amusement park, the Bears use a magic potion to get bigger.

added.title: Triple T Tigers
added.description: The Bears meet three cool tiger brothers. Grizz wants to be just like the oldest Tiger, TK, but he may not be the best role model.

added.title: Panda's Family
added.description: While exploring a lantern festival, the Bears encounter Panda's long-lost family.

added.title: A Tale of Two Ice Bears
added.description: The Bears accidentally clone Ice Bear and Ice Bear has a hard time adjusting.

added.title: Unica
added.description: The Bears join forces with Unica, the ultimate forest protector.

added.title: Last Mom Standing
added.description: When Chef's Mom and Leshawna's Grandmother drop their loved ones off at the same time, it kicks off a dangerous competition for who is the most caring mother-figure.

added.title: Carmageddon
added.description: Duncan is rattled when Chef, tired of having his car destroyed, buys a new one that is completely indestructible.

added.title: Sugar & Spice & Lightning & Frights
added.description: When two new kids show up at the daycare Duncan and Leshawna take issue with, not what makes them different, but what makes them similar to the newbies.

added.title: Breaking Bite
added.description: Beth becomes the big dog on campus after she bites Duncan, but being the big dog is a dangerous thing, especially when you didn't actually bite anybody!

added.title: I Dream of Meanie
added.description: When Cody keeps screaming in his sleep Gwen and Duncan take a trip into Cody's dreams to see what is scaring him.

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Bottle Catch
added.description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Block Party
added.description: Apple and Onion have to outwit a mean duck who's taken over their building's roof.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple decides to help Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Lil Noodle
added.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

added.title: Gyranoid of the Future
added.description: Apple and Onion are dead set on riding Gyranoid of the Future, the craziest roller coaster at the carnival.

added.title: Fun Proof
added.description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".

added.title: Whale Spotting
added.description: In order to see a rare whale, Apple and Onion have to become members of an exclusive club, but one of them doesn't quite have the chops.

added.title: Subway
added.description: The Bears are stranded on a subway platform after missing their train. But while waiting, the Bears are challenged with recovering some lost items.

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: In order to appear on a successful kids show, Nom Nom must successfully complete anger management, with Grizz as his partner.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Cellie
added.description: Fed up with sharing, Panda forbids his brothers from using his cellphone any longer. But when the brothers get their own super advanced smartphones, Panda starts to succumb to crippling jealousy.

added.title: Chicken and Waffles
added.description: Panda needs to meet his brothers at the most exclusive restaurant in town. But when he loses his contacts lenses and can't see, Panda needs Charlie's help to get him into the city.

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Take 10
added.description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: During a stop at the superstore Shoppe, Ben and Gwen are transformed into babies by nanny-gone-nuts Nanny Nightmare, who will stop at nothing to reshape the world in the image of her daycare.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: Animo Farm
added.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: Steven and Lars spend some time together.

added.title: The Trial
added.description: Steven goes on trial.

added.title: Off Colors
added.description: Steven finds some unusual new allies.

added.title: Lars' Head
added.description: Lars finally lets Steven in.

added.title: Dewey Wins
added.description: Steven helps Mayor Dewey run a difficult campaign.

added.title: Gemcation
added.description: Greg and the Gems take Steven on vacation to help him relax.

added.title: Raising the Barn
added.description: Pumpkin goes missing!

added.title: Back to the Kindergarten
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Peridot try to spruce up the Kindergarten.

added.title: Sadie Killer
added.description: Steven and the Cool Kids start a band, but they have trouble finding their sound.

added.title: Kevin Party
added.description: Kevin is throwing a party, and Steven is invited.

added.title: Lars of the Stars
added.description: Lars rises to the occasion.

added.title: Jungle Moon
added.description: Stevonnie finds themself alone on an adventure.

added.title: Your Mother and Mine
added.description: Steven takes Garnet to meet some of his new friends.

added.title: The Big Show
added.description: Steven shoots a documentary that follows a local band as they get their first big break.

added.title: Letters to Lars
added.description: Steven writes about the latest news of Beach City.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Conquest of Cuteness
added.description: King Snuggadoodle and the Huggaboopies invade Finn and Jake's tree house.

added.title: Morituri Te Salutamus
added.description: Finn and Jake are trapped in the arena of the Fight King and must face gladiators to set themselves free.

added.title: Hitman
added.description: The Ice King tries to win Princess Bubblegum over with his love potion.

added.title: Too Young
added.description: Princess Bubblegum's uncle attempts to usurp Ooo's throne.

added.title: The Monster
added.description: Lumpy Space Princess's parents have come to ask Finn and Jake to find their daughter and convince her to come home.

added.title: Still
added.description: Finn and Jake find themselves paralyzed from the neck down and at the Ice King's mercy!

added.title: Wizard Battle
added.description: Every couple hundred of years or so, all the wizards in Ooo assemble for Wizard Sport, a fantastic, wizards-only battle royale.

added.title: Adventure Time with Fionna and Cake
added.description: It's a parallel universe where we explore the adventures of Fiona and Cake from the land of Aaa!

added.title: What Was Missing
added.description: Finn and Jake do battle with a powerful door lord.

added.title: Memory of a Memory
added.description: To save Marceline from a sleep spell, Finn and Jake must enter her mind and find the wake spell deep inside her memory.

added.title: Thank You
added.description: The Snow Golem and his beseeching pup pay a visit to the Fire Kingdom.

added.title: Paper Pete
added.description: The pages of the books in the Ooo library turn to Finn and Jake for help before the evil Moldari destroy them.

added.title: Another Way
added.description: The tears of a crying Cyclops just might heal Finn and Jake's broken toes.

added.title: Ghost Princess
added.description: Finn and Jake try to solve Ghost Princess' unsolved murder.

added.title: Dad's Dungeon
added.description: Jake's Dad appears in a holographic message with a mysterious challenge for Finn and Jake.

added.title: Starter Pack
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to stop Muscle Man from messing with Thomas.

added.title: Payback/Party Bus
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Wallpaper Man
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: 150-Piece Kit
added.description: Benson wants to prove that he performed a famous drum solo.

added.title: Bald Spot
added.description: Muscle Man wants to hide his bald spot at all costs.

added.title: Guy's Night
added.description: Pops wants to beat the milk challenge to prove he's one of the guys.

added.title: One Pull Up
added.description: Rigby needs to do one pull-up so he can pass the park physical.

added.title: T.G.I. Tuesday
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby and Eileen want to celebrate Margaret's new internship before she has to quit the coffee shop.

added.title: Firework Run
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby and Muscle Man have to get fireworks for an event at the park because they used the ones Benson got.

added.title: The Longest Weekend
added.description: Muscle Man has to make it through a week without contacting Starla.

added.title: Sandwich of Death
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to find a cure for the Death Sandwich before Benson dies.

added.title: Ace Balthazar Lives
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to reunite the lead guitarist of Adrenaline with his band.

added.title: Do or Diaper
added.description: Mordecai has to kiss Margaret by the end of the week or else wear a diaper.

added.title: Quips
added.description: Skips has to tell his cousin Tips to stop telling bad jokes.

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Toast of the Town/Divide and Conquer
added.description: Toast of the Town: When the Mayor rubs Chemical X on his head for hair growth, all of him grows and stomps through Townsville./Divide and Conquer: When the Amoeba Boys learn how to divide, they multiply wreaking havoc as the many amoebas descend upon Townsville.

added.title: Save Mojo/Substitute Creature
added.description: Save Mojo: An animal activist group sets out to protect Mojo, ensuring that he can behave like the naturally evil monkey that he is./Substitute Creature: A substitute teacher comes to Pokey Oaks and the girls are sure that this creature teacher is up to no good.

added.title: The Boys Are Back in Town
added.description: Him brings the Rowdyruff Boys back, protecting them from the girls' feminine wiles.

added.title: Pee Pee G's/Boy Toys
added.description: The Pee Pee G's: When the girls wake up to discover their bed is wet, none of them want to admit that they are the guilty party./Boy Toys: The girls allow Princess to become a Powerpuff Girl when they realize they need help trying to defeat the Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Seed No Evil/City of Clipsville
added.description: Seed No Evil: When a prehistoric caveman thaws out in Townsville, the girls must stop him from stealing the Mayor's seeds./City of Clipsville: The girls reminisce on their adventures in these new, never-before-seen clips!

added.title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
added.description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

added.title: Power-Noia
added.description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

added.title: Not So Secret Service
added.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

added.title: Worship
added.description: When the Fashionistas unveil their new mind controlling perfume, the Powerpuff Girls must find a way to stop them before Townsville falls under their spell.

added.title: Blossom3
added.description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Trouble Clef
added.description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

added.title: Save the Date
added.description: Ms. Keane is nervous about a first date.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: Blundercup
added.description: Buttercup is knocked off-kilter by a mysterious force.

added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

added.title: The Long Skate Home
added.description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: Salamander
added.description: When the professor is kidnapped, the girls must go to a mysterious island to save him.

added.title: Checkin' Out!
added.description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

added.title: Spoooooky Game
added.description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

added.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
added.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Action Forest
added.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Fire & Nice
added.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Crushing Defeat
added.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: Pet Pet
added.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: Clarence Loves Shoopy
added.description: When Clarence discovers that one of his neighbors is the grumpy school recess proctor Ms. Shoop - he gets a glimpse of her home life and decides the only things she's missing are some friends. Clarence sets out on a mission to match the cranky oddball Shoop with some new pals!

added.title: Public Radio
added.description: After listening to a public radio broadcast during class, Clarence is inspired to record a radio interview of his own featuring his buddy Sumo. When Ms. Baker hears the charming interview, she calls in a favor and gets Clarence a spot on the actual Aberdale Public Radio! The search is on - to find the perfect interview subject for his big day.

added.title: Chad and the Marathon
added.description: When Chad realizes his lazy habits might be rubbing off on Clarence, he decides to participate in the Aberdale Marathon. However, the athletic Chad doesn't know the first thing about being a runner, and must enlist the help of Clarence to train!

added.title: Officer Moody
added.description: Pieces of Mr. Reese's past are revealed when his old partner on the police force, Officer Moody, visits Aberdale Elementary.

added.title: Gilben's Different
added.description: Gilben's newly sprouted peach fuzz sparks a discussion about puberty that ultimately convinces Clarence to act more like an adult.

added.title: Cool Guy Clarence
added.description: When Clarence meets JT, the kid who mows their lawn, he finds a fast friend who shows him some cool new music, a new outlook on life and a sweet rat-tail! Clarence leans into the rat tail lifestyle, discovering a whole new side of Aberdale he never knew existed.

added.title: Just Wait in the Car
added.description: As Mary runs errands, Clarence waits in the car and struggles to fight boredom.

added.title: Missing Cat
added.description: When Chelsea accidentally lets her pet cat Crumbles out, the cat goes missing! Reluctant to ask for help, she struggles to find the cat before anyone realizes it's gone. It's up to cat whisperer Clarence to interject and find Crumbles, whether Chelsea wants his help or not!

added.title: Big Trouble in Little Aberdale
added.description: After stumbling upon a mysterious new kid in their neighborhood , Clarence, Jeff and Sumo decide to take the kid out on the town showing him the fun of junk food, arcades and soda! However, this new lifestyle may be more then the new kid bargained for.

added.title: Dare Day
added.description: With Jeff on vacation, Sumo and Clarence egg each other on in a series of increasingly absurd and extreme dares. But will one of them put a stop to this dare day, before it goes too far?

added.title: Bucky and the Howl
added.description: After Clarence learns Sumo's in the school musical, he joins up and enthusiastically promotes the show. On opening night with a packed house, stage fright takes hold of Sumo and he runs off leaving Clarence to go on alone.

added.title: Worm Bin
added.description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Birthday
added.description: Jeff and Sumo expect no one to show at Clarence's birthday party, just like last year. When dozens of kids arrive, the boys struggle to get face time with Clarence, the popular party host.

added.title: Tree of Life
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo make it their mission to climb a really tall tree before it's set to be chopped down. As they scale higher and higher their reality begins to slip away.

added.title: Lame Station
added.description: Pizza Steve tries desperately to make the others in the RV interested in his new game console.

added.title: Space Oddity
added.description: In the year 3021, the gang's intergalactic mission goes awry when a strange alien creature infiltrates their ship.

added.title: Relaxation Land
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's relaxing weekend getaway quickly becomes a spooky nightmare for Pizza Steve.

added.title: Land of the Lost Shadows
added.description: When pieces of their shadows are stolen by a shadow demon, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must travel to the Land of Lost Shadows in order to retrieve them.

added.title: Pizza Eve
added.description: Uncle Grandpa falls for Pizza Steve's "girlfriend" and ends up in serious danger.

added.title: The Return of Aunt Grandma
added.description: Aunt Grandma is back and still bent on ruining Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Messy Bessy
added.description: Seth must clean his room and learn to be a neater person in order to keep Messy Bessy from making his life a nightmare.

added.title: Memory Foam
added.description: When a new mattress sucks away all of Pizza Steve's memories, Uncle Grandpa and the crew must find a way to get them back.

added.title: Even More Shorts
added.description: Weird Man apprehends a dangerous foreign criminal, Belly Bag discovers a cat stuck in the RV tree, and Uncle Grandpa hosts a space exploration program on this new collection of shorts.

added.title: Fleas Help Me
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang help their K9 pal, Charlie Burgers, get rid of his flea infestation.

added.title: Wicked Shades
added.description: When Pizza Steve borrows Uncle Grandpa's sunglasses, he sees things in a whole new light.

added.title: Except for Cooper
added.description: A young boy must learn to eat his spinach in order to save Uncle Grandpa and the others from a rowdy gang of evil vegetables.

added.title: In the Clouds
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a boy get his head out of the clouds and focused on his history test.

added.title: The Lepre-Con
added.description: On a St. Patrick's Day trip to Ireland, Uncle Grandpa and the gang cross paths with a sneaky leprechaun.

added.title: Uncle Fashion
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a young boy who wants to be a fashion designer by taking him somewhere his style will be appreciated.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: Prime Mates/Coupe D'Etat
added.description: Prime Mates: Back when Mojo Jojo tried to take over the world with primates, there was one monkey who didn't get his due: Mopey Popo. Now, Mopey is back to try and be just as evil as Mojo intended./Coupe D'Etat: When the Professor tricks out his car, the girls realize that this K.A.R.R. is taking the Professor away from them both figuratively and literally.

added.title: Silent Treatment/Sweet "n" Sour
added.description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

added.title: Makes Zen to Me/Say Uncle
added.description: Makes Zen to Me: When Buttercup gets a fortune cookie saying peace lies within, the most violent of Powerpuffs sets out on a quest for inner peace./Say Uncle: The girls' go to pick up the Professor's brother at the train station, but mistake him for a wild-man being transported to the circus.

added.title: Buff's BFF
added.description: When Buff befriends Mr. Freeze's snowcrawler Snowy, the other Batwheels bristle at the thought of hanging out with a "bad guy…" so Buff sets out to change their minds.

added.title: Up in the Air
added.description: After he causes the Batwing to crash, Bam becomes obsessed with making it up to her during a high-stakes aerial mission against Penguin and his giant ducky blimp.

added.title: Wake Up Dance
added.description: It's nearly dawn on the farm and a scarecrow called Sunny joins Ella to wake up the animals.

added.title: Halloween Dress Up
added.description: It's Halloween and there's a monster, a skeleton, a vampire, a dinosaur and a pirate on the farm!

added.title: Jelly Jam Jam
added.description: Ella helps Mei make some delicious jams using fresh produce from Lellobee City Farm.

added.title: Yes Yes Vegetables Song
added.description: Woolly Sheep sets up his stall at the farm. He's going to make everyone some winter vegetable soup.

added.title: Boo Boo Song
added.description: Ella, Heidi and Pablo all have a tumble whilst dancing. Ella has a plan - "boogie off the boo boo"!

added.title: Mary Had a Little Lamb
added.description: Ella and Mei are going to the playground. Lettie the lamb follows them so she can be close to Ella!

added.title: Ella's Campfire Sing-A-Long
added.description: Ella has her first camping experience. It's time to gather round the fire for a special sing-a-long.

added.title: 5 Little Monkeys
added.description: Ella has to look after five mischievous baby monkeys that Sami the vet has brought to the farm.

added.title: Animal sounds on the farm (I Hear With My Little Ear)
added.description: Ella and Rishi play a listening game. They hear expected sounds and an unexpected one! SLURP!

added.title: Do the ABC Dance!
added.description: Ella does the ABC Dance with Mei, Heidi and Lettie under balloon shaped bunting of the alphabet.

added.title: Yes Yes Bed Time
added.description: None of the animals want to go to bed. A cuddle from Ella is the only thing that makes them settle.

added.title: Twinkle Twinkle
added.description: Bee gets one of Ella's glow in the dark stars stuck on their tummy and amazes the animals.

added.title: L-L-Lellogames
added.description: Mei has set up an obstacle course for Ella and friends that turns farmyard chores into a fun game!

added.title: Down by the Lellobee Farm
added.description: Ella uses her tools to pick vegetables, scatter grain, plant flowers, dig weeds and rake leaves.

added.title: Winter Football Soccer Song
added.description: Ella and friends take on the away team for a friendly game of three a side football on a snowy day.

added.title: Back To School
added.description: Ella creates a school set up at the farm and teaches her animal friends what school is all about!

added.title: Old Macdonald
added.description: Ella and Bee play a game of hide and seek on the farm with Carlos, Pablo, Lettie and Heidi.

added.title: Stargazing Lullaby
added.description: Mei and Ella do some stargazing. They see a bear, a giraffe, a dolphin and an eagle in the sky!

removed.title: Sophie, the Bakuganist/Midnight Train Battle!
removed.description: Sophie, the Bakuganist: Magnus is on the trail of the illegal Baku-brawling devices and, is looking to cut off the supply at its source. When he witnesses an illegal deal going down, he knows it's up to him to go after the shipment to keep the illegal devices off the street./Midnight Train Battle!: Sophie Judson Warfield, a wealthy activist with the Citizens to Save Bakugan Society, is working to put an end to all Bakugan brawling. Her latest target is the Awesome Brawlers themselves. When Wynton doesn't take Sophie seriously, the encounter quickly turns into an all-out Bakugan brawl.

removed.title: Kung Fu Master/A Battle of Popularity
removed.description: Kung Fu Master: Dan's first match-up of the Bakugan battle league is the Chinese Champion Brawler: Zhao. His opponent is a deeply focused, and serious brawler, who uses Kung Fu techniques in battle. It's going to take all Dan and Drago's focus and strength to get through this opponent!/A Battle of Popularity: Shun and Wynton's first match-ups in the Bakugan battle league take place at the same time. Even though they're not battling each other, Wynton can't help getting a little competitive with Shun, bragging that he can get the crowd cheering louder than Shun. The brawls quickly turn into a popularity contest, instead of a Bakugan battle!

removed.title: Baku-Gear/Bakugan Rock!
removed.description: Baku-Gear: The Awesome Brawlers are excited over their discovery of Baku-Gear, and want to get some footage of it in action. While they're filming, an underclassman named Trey challenges Dan to battle. Who will emerge victorious in the impromptu battle?/Bakugan Rock!: Baku-gear has shown up twice for Dan and Drago and it's starting to eat away at the other awesome brawlers. It's time they take it into their own hands. When Lia and Wynton go up against the rockin' new brawlers in town, they show Dan and Drago that they are not the only one who can summon this cool new tool!

removed.title: The Past Revealed/Run! A Storm's on the Way
removed.description: The Past Revealed: After getting lost in maze with Lia, Ajit remembers the day he met Pharol and Auxilataur. He finally can explain how he was able to partner with golden Bakugan, but Ajit's story is interrupted by a familiar face - Storm!/Run! A Storm's on the Way: Still upset that Ajit has given up his life as a phantom thief, Storm rolls out Hydranoid x Aquos and attacks! Ajit and Lia take off running through the maze as Storm gives chase.

removed.title: The Bakugan Battle League Begins/Riot vs. Ajit
removed.description: The Bakugan Battle League Begins: The qualifying rounds for the Bakugan Battle league are taking place all around Los Volmos. The Awesome Brawlers all make it through into the tournament without a hitch, that is all but Dan. Dan faces an old rival in Trey, who's back with a few tricks up his sleeve./Riot vs. Ajit: The Bakugan battle league is finally here and 16 brawlers have qualified to enter including all the Awesome Brawlers. The first round will feature a brawl between China Riot and the golden Bakugan brawler, Agit!

removed.title: Dusk Industries Under Attack/Taking Dan Back
removed.description: Dusk Industries Under Attack: "Bad Dan" has his taken his rampage to Dusk Industries and this time he has help spreading the chaos and destruction, he's joined by Sophie, McQ, Everett, Storm and Haavik! The Awesome Brawlers are quickly on the scene try to bring an end to the show of destruction./ Taking Dan Back: "Bad Dan" with Haavik's crew and their fusion Bakugan continue the rampage at Dusk Industries. The Awesome Brawlers, with some help from Magnus, are determined to an end to this show of destruction and get their friend back!

removed.title: The Lady and the Queen/The AB's Silver Screen Debut
removed.description: The Lady and the Queen: China Riot finds a new Bakugan: Barbetra. But this buzzy new Bakugan is a bit timid on the battleground. Riot takes her on as her new project to turn her into the battle queen she knows she can be./The AB's Silver Screen Debut: Lord Brakken and Duran have teamed up and are now the Bakugan film business. They look to the Awesome Brawlers for their expertise in both Bakugan culture and film making to get their movie made!

removed.title: In the Darkness/Indecisive Emily
removed.description: An encounter with Storm and his trick rose leaves Magnus temporarily blinded and unable to brawl. With the help of an unlikely partner, Magnus pursues Storm in an attempt to defeat him and restore his vision./ Emily obtains a second Bakugan named Chrissy. It's soon obvious that Emily is having trouble brawling with both Chrissy and Webam, and it's up to Dan, Drago and Gillator to teach them how to brawl as a team.

removed.title: Once More into the Maze/Grandpas in the Wild
removed.description: Once More into the Maze: Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett were spotted at the ruins where the great core cell is housed! Alarmed by the report from Benton Dusk, the Awesome Brawlers head to the Yucatan Peninsula to investigate./Grandpas in the Wild: During an all-out brawl with Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, the Awesome Brawlers are hit with an attack that sends everyone spiraling to various parts of the maze. Split up from the rest of the gang, Wynton and Lightning find themselves in a strange unfamiliar part of the maze. While trying to get their bearings, they discover some new golden allies.

removed.title: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!/Magnus
removed.description: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing./Magnus: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

removed.title: Bakugan Wynton/The Boy from Brazil
removed.description: Bakugan Wynton: Wynton has a new device that tracks down Bakugan! Right out of the gate the device works and, Wynton meets: Batrix. Like his name, Batrix is a little batty, and these two are certainly in for a "batty" first adventure./The Boy from Brazil: The Awesome Brawlers are off to a soccer match! In the process of doing so Shun discovers a new Bakugan friend, the boisterous Ramparian, and a new foe in Brazilian soccer star: Pepe.

removed.title: The Eclipse/Follow Haavik!
removed.description: There's an eclipse happening over Los Volmos, but there's something even more strange going on. Dan and Drago quickly realize something's up; no one seems like themselves today. The two need to get to the bottom of it and return things back to normal./ Magnus and Ajit spot Haavik on the street and decide to follow him, but the shape shifting Haavik is on to them. It's not long before an epic brawl breaks out between them - Five Faction Fusion Sabrus vs. Nillious X Darkus and Pharol.

removed.title: Golden Bakugan Encounter/Ties of Gold
removed.description: Golden Bakugan Encounter: Dan and Shun, split up from the rest of Awesome Brawlers, are traveling in through the maze when they discover McQ. It turns out McQ is seeking a golden Bakugan. When the boys go in for a closer look, they are startled by an old friend, and together confront McQ./Ties of Gold: The now reunited Awesome Brawlers are once again confronted by Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, who are on the hunt for golden Bakugan. With tired Bakugan, the Awesome Brawlers will have to give it their all to defend against this evil.

removed.title: Brawler Headhunting/Lightning's Entrance Exam
removed.description: Brawler Headhunting: As acting president of Kazami International, Shun is called upon to entertain another new young CEO Luca Schmidt, who's interested in doing business with the Kazami International. But Shun quickly realizes something is up when Luca tries woo him over to his brawling team - the Glanz Five. /Lightning's Entrance Exam: The Awesome Brawlers may be world famous heroes, but that doesn't mean they get out of going to school. They are still regular kids, doing regular kid things. But teachers may have something to say when Lightening decides he wants to join his buddies in the classroom.

removed.title: The Mysterious Boy/A New Power
removed.description: The Mysterious Boy: After stopping Tiko's rampage, the Awesome Brawlers have become world-famous heroes and Bakugan-mania sweeps the globe. With the Bakugan boom, brawling has been reinvented as a sporting game. In celebration of the Awesome Brawlers efforts, a tournament is being held in their honor. But the battles are quickly cut short when a rogue brawler and his golden Bakugan crash the event./A New Power: A Rogue brawler, Agit and his golden Bakugan have crashed the Awesome Brawlers party. Who is this brawler? How can he control a Golden Bakugan? Only one way to find out - Bakugan Brawl! Dan and Drago go head to head with the outsides to get to the bottom of it. Outmatched by their opponent, Dan and Drago get a little help from a new powerful weapon - Baku-Gear.

removed.title: Nightmare/Bad Dan
removed.description: Nightmare: Dan hasn't been sleeping well lately. No "sleep brawling" this time, but he's constantly tossing and turning. It turns out, Dan's dreams have been hijacked by Haavik, who's trying to spread his vision of chaos and destruction to Dan!/Bad Dan: Haavik has taken control of Dan and sends him on a Bakugan rampage! With "Bad Dan" causing all kinds of havoc and destruction, the rest of the Awesome Brawlers have no choice but to roll out to try to contain "Bad Dan".

removed.title: The Tokyo Catastrophe/Bakugan Battle League Finale
removed.description: The Tokyo Catastrophe: Haavik has highjacked the Bakugan Battle league - Tokyo Edition! He's been using the tournament as a platform for his sinister plot to bring chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo./Bakugan Battle League Finale: Haavik unleashes an army of unruly Bakugan to bring his own brand of chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo. It's all hands-on-deck to stop the invasion, and foil Haavik's plot.

removed.title: Bakugan Uproar/The Fusion Bakugan Sabrus
removed.description: While the Awesome Brawlers' Bakugan squabble about what to watch on TV at Studio D, Haavik unleashes his newly created five-faction fusion Bakugan: Sabrus on the city of Los Volmos./ The Awesome Brawlers are in pursuit of Haavik and his new Bakugan, Sabrus but all they can find is the trail of destruction that Sabrus has left behind. They need to figure out where Haavik and his Bakugan will strike next and put an end to his rampage.

removed.title: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition/Battle Royal
removed.description: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition: It's the start of the Bakugan Battle League - Toyko edition! The first round will be a Battle Royale style competition, where only half the competitors will make it through to the next round. Along with the Awesome brawlers the field of competitors is filled with familiar friends and foes./Battle Royal: The first round of the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo edition continues. The Awesome Brawler's and their Bakugan battle their way through the challenge and face off against tough competitors.

removed.title: The AB Bakugan Battle League!
removed.description: With all the mayhem and destruction Haavik is causing, the Awesome Brawlers decide that a bit of Bakugan brawling is the perfect distraction to take their minds off all the trouble. With the help of some friends, they start the Awesome Brawler Bakugan Battle league!/ The Awesome Brawler's Bakugan Battle league rages on. Just as the semifinal round comes to a close, an uninvited guest crashes the party, bringing an alarming end to the battle league.

removed.title: Farewell, Phantom Thief
removed.description: After being exposed as a phantom thief in the Bakugan battle league, the Awesome Brawlers are concerned about Ajit, but have no idea of his whereabouts. Dan is particularly affected by Ajit's disappearance and sets out to find him to get some answers./Ajit is out to set right all the wrong doings of his phantom thief past. When he attempts to break into a museum to return artifacts, his mentor Storm is waiting for him. A Bakugan brawl breaks out between two when Storm rolls out his new Bakugan: Cimoga.

removed.title: Tiko's Back?!/Arise, Ultimate Infinity!
removed.description: Tiko's Back?!: In order to make Sabrus a 6 faction fusion Bakugan, Haavik heads into the maze to try to capture a golden Bakugan who has brought "mayhem and destruction" to Earth once before - Tiko!/Arise, Ultimate Infinity!: The Awesome Brawlers manage to thwart Haavik's attempt to fuse Tiko with Sabrus, but Haavik ends up escaping with the golden Bakugan, Pyravian. Now the Awesome Brawlers must track down Haavik before he can form his ultimate 6 faction fusion Bakugan.

removed.title: Magnus P.I.
removed.description: There's a been a string of thefts and each one has involved a Bakugan. The AAAnimus security force have decided the only brawler who could be responsible is: Magnus. The shock of this accusation sets Magnus off to takes justice in his own hands and go after the thief himself./Magnus foils the latest burglary attempt by the phantom thief, and in doing so, discovers the brawler partners with a golden Bakugan.  Magnus is now more interested in a brawl, than stopping any crime.

removed.title: Haavik's Final Show/Miracle Planet
removed.description: Haavik's Final Show: It's the final stage of Haavik's Bakugan Battle League: Dan and Drago Infinity vs. Haavik and his six-faction fusion Bakugan, Sabrus. Once again, the fate of two worlds, Earth and Vestoria rests in the hands of the Awesome Brawlers!/ Miracle Planet: The epic clash between Drago Infinty and Sabrus rages on. The winner of this clash of titans will decide the fate Earth and Vestroia.

removed.title: Haavik's Challenge/Storm Haavik's Tower
removed.description: Haavik's Challenge: Haavik has crashed the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan League, and challenges the Awesome Brawlers in a battle league of his own!/ Storm Haavik's Tower: In order to keep Earth and Vestroia safe and rescue Drago, the Awesome Brawlers agree to enter Haavik's Bakugan Battle League, and race toward Haavik's tower for the final showdown.
